Did you know that artificial colors like Red 40 are banned in Europe, yet allowed by the US FDA? 😳

We know products like Biena's are made without artificial flavors/colors are better for us. But why? 

Let's take a look at Red 40...(this is a super common one in snacks, sweets, beverages and baked goods). While FDA approved in the US, this additive is known to impair children with ADHD as well as small traces of benzidine or other carcinogens have been found contaminated in the product. 🤯 Oh and by the way - the only purpose of this dye is to make your foods brighter shades of red, like a cherry popsicle or strawberry yogurt.

We don't use artificial colors because YOU DON't NEED THEM. We believe food products should be made up of exactly that, food!

P.S. Yes, this is an actual beaker of Red 40 artificial color! (Definitely doesn't look like food to me).
